snippet.textDisplay: I love the east coast, but honestly, it's not as clean as most of the western US. There are so many people and cultures with varying standards of cleanliness. And the people of New York and other large cities of the east coast mostly live stacked on top of each other - hundreds of folks may use the same front door, elevator buttons, stair railings, escalator railings, cabs, subway handles, etc.. And if the virus can be airborne (which I have a hard time believing it can't) many even share air vents and duct work in apartment and office buildings. It's their way of life. True social distancing is just much, much harder in these large cities.
